The JSE closed weaker on Monday, mainly on
the back of weakness recorded across most blue-chip stocks. The local bourse failed to take a leaf from
the firmer close recorded in Chinese equities which saw the Shanghai Composite
Index close 0.28% firmer, while the Hang Seng rose 0.97%. Stocks in Japan
struggled which saw the Nikkei closing 0.22% weaker. Stocks traded mostly flat
in Europe as they struggled to find a catalyst for direction. In the USA,
market participants are waiting for results from Google parent, Alphabet which
is expected to release results after the US markets’ close on Monday. On the currency market, the US dollar was
mildly firmer against a basket of major currencies. The rand traded mostly
firmer despite this US dollar strength as it peaked at a session high of
R14.30/$. At 17.00 CAT, it was trading 0.48% firmer at R14.31/$. On the JSE, Naspers [JSE:NPN] came under
pressure despite its associate Tencent Holdings closing 1.72% firmer at
$HK390.60 on the Hang Seng. Naspers eventually closed 0.2% weaker at R3685.43.
Platinum miners also struggled on the day which saw Anglo American Platinum [JSE:AMS]
close amongst the day’s biggest losers after it lost 5.85% to close at R720.22,
while Impala Platinum [JSE:IMP] weakened by 5.32% to close at R60.12. Gold
miner AngloGold Ashanti [JSE:ANG] fell 4.17% to close at R172.00, while Harmony
Gold [JSE:HAR] dropped 3.28% as it closed at R24.76. Other significant movers
lower included Blue Label Telecoms [JSE:BLU] which lost 4.62% to close at R4.75,
Fortress REIT [JSE:FFA] which fell 2.84% to R19.18, and Bidvest [JSE:BVT] which
closed at R216.18 after dropping 1.74%. Gains were fairly modest on the day with
decent gains being recorded for listed property stocks. Rebosis Property Fund
[JSE:REB] managed to gain 3.68% as it closed at R1.41, Delta Property added 5.49%
to close at R1.92, and Intu Properties [JSE:ITU] gained 1.83% to close at R18.40.
Rand hedge British American Tobacco [JSE:BTI] firmed by 1.14% to close at R554.83,
while Mondi PLC [JSE:MNP] closed 0.67% higher at R317.00. Retailers also inched
higher on the day which saw gains being recorded for Shoprite [JSE:SHP] which
added 1.04% to close at R177.65, as well as Massmart [JSE:MSM] which closed
0.77% higher at R91.09. The JSE All-Share index eventually closed
0.54% weaker while the JSE Top-40 index lost 0.52%. The Financials index barely
closed firmer as it added 0.08%, while the Industrials and Resources lost 0.28%
and 0.83% respectively. At 17.00 CAT, Palladium had plummeted 6.61%
to trade at $1368.75/Oz, Platinum was down 0.82% at $891.55/Oz, and Gold was
0.49% weaker at $1279.75/Oz. Brent crude retreated over the weekend as
market participants fretted over Donald Trump’s calls for OPEC to take measures
to reduce oil prices. The commodity was trading 0.085 firmer at $71.72/barrel
just after the JSE close.